intro: Peucedanum multivittatum var. dissectum, commonly known as the dissected cow parsley, is a flowering plant native to parts of Europe and Asia. It belongs to the Apiaceae family, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its finely divided, fern-like leaves. The plant produces small, white to pale yellow flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the family. It thrives in moist, shady environments and is often found in woodlands or along stream banks. Its ornamental value comes from its delicate foliage and subtle floral display.
